{"type":"message","id":"835b3429","parentId":"cdd6a9a5","timestamp":"2026-05-14T03:37:04.297Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Searching for connection options**\n\nI see that I need to connect via Telegram only since WhatsApp isn't enabled right now. So, I might need to find a \"connect agent\" that can clarify how to integrate this with WhatsApp. Maybe I could look into some local documents for WhatsApp? I should probably do a search to see what resources or documentation are available that might help me out with this situation. Let's figure this out together!","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_080f36febbd39781016a05435d6a4c8196aa7ad4396714e354\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqBUNfDu0aKZwyFu2SvODBpN-nf12ef1oSXxSlH3j1ufxY34Pfh1muq-2JWWT1tNqlA9yvJw_KGqgnjNuYvDbO3YM8iTDhTeVmt3NDJag2cvIiYbsczgMdo3IntEIXxCrixLgjOsdaWDfTA9HfEdI-AvBptv-FBCTsgofPP0FD_S7PL4P8dxF5rmxwHs8Io_HswaLBrQ4nFRESBPxj1WMqe_hZYThbeKmGihDZWiLaBhImTee7cPSdYutuIwg972lG6OWMWHEbsnaZrvsk7naxBCcd3jQvG54Gy5mp7QPJq1Cnq2yfwgFDBJ-sUR1Eawy1g-yddjaDLigPrWPXKJx9gBwJyUfq7o0LvqTExmR7gwNMOeoikqs7CIDupR4MzOATGeZtKEcM9Y_WKVKzzpwSbzBR6X3hAaMxGy2PpzuG-UjOQjMwwAV9Os5MaipSkizOduhI8OIh5LfWd_4mxRBN5rbJbL9Nwqlq7JwmVcQUohsicJilqf38p4tfMgb6kakvgnSiO55Gn_fjTKPdnG7G0YbeXvanSXpKTmBOc29fIQzg_NKt-W4J-2knpVM7FAsjfjL0slaCnN4hf0Xh937YFkuRi-5Vf1HjQsuJCGARXA1ZouVQEXncW7lrg0A_ANR7KVyfqFFAl937QmFIvEFGu02VtE01N3H_x4C1kgABIhdEwbsruuiMHMmn0zSe_WGNraOZFd4Cst40fP1tQYDAcNhHz46qye0jznf8fdvUL1WxWraralsEuYgUtUzeX93PgX3jCHGJpv-YwoYzXg26l0E9Q8jh7wRbELBY-XhM9FHB7hfRVOKRVii6nlyQ743B9mc2JYzZYnwk3YbKu6ZaydW5_STJJKA_ZQpxkyZRJfHBWm7TpTEEeMaCASt9fMQPLD7W1hwUc5BzR9AhNRC9kJMtXSeXdLDAVBlzMCbGXIVo283pApvrV7sQrWsBwv6xfQKOdEcJRc7a_3vuN4L3WSq69rDmidx9sqYRVvwqA6cX65ovanfqIBqWdyrAZpAQ817wGqCHm6A7jJjwFzUJN6RwcpPMmv942AitSQY_tU_AW8RT7LP1_9HC8TEiU_1ucpwIgbEtHYDpJ8pMzOovr9DYrPwWOyCh7n_h1hi_711DJEA=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Searching for connection options**\\n\\nI see that I need to connect via Telegram only since WhatsApp isn't enabled right now. So, I might need to find a \\\"connect agent\\\" that can clarify how to integrate this with WhatsApp. Maybe I could look into some local documents for WhatsApp? I should probably do a search to see what resources or documentation are available that might help me out with this situation. Let's figure this out together!\"}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_vZiZT4za56uZklotJst64Uu7|fc_080f36febbd39781016a05435f9ca48196998ad6c0fbbe5d9a","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -R \"WhatsApp\\|whatsapp\" -n /usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs | head -80","workdir":"/root/.openclaw/workspace-sharkzap","yieldMs":1000,"timeout":30}}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.5","usage":{"input":1407,"output":109,"cacheRead":83456,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":84972,"cost":{"input":0.0070350000000000005,"output":0.00327,"cacheRead":0.041728,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.052033}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778729818223,"responseId":"resp_080f36febbd39781016a05435b20908196b39c02e8fde5ed64"}}
{"type":"message","id":"0e295e0a","parentId":"835b3429","timestamp":"2026-05-14T03:37:04.467Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_vZiZT4za56uZklotJst64Uu7|fc_080f36febbd39781016a05435f9ca48196998ad6c0fbbe5d9a","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/mantis.md:7:  - Adding Discord, Slack, WhatsApp, or other live transport scenarios\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/mantis.md:535:- WhatsApp: QR login, re-identification, message delivery, media, reactions.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/agent-runtimes.md:22:| Channel       | Telegram, Discord, Slack, WhatsApp    | Where messages enter and leave OpenClaw.                            |\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/features.md:12:    Discord, iMessage, Signal, Slack, Telegram, WhatsApp, WebChat, and more with a single Gateway.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/features.md:35:- Built-in channels include Discord, Google Chat, iMessage (legacy), IRC, Signal, Slack, Telegram, WebChat, and WhatsApp\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:9:Run multiple _isolated_ agents — each with its own workspace, state directory (`agentDir`), and session history — plus multiple channel accounts (e.g. two WhatsApps) in one running Gateway. Inbound messages are routed to the right agent through bindings.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:11:An **agent** here is the full per-persona scope: workspace files, auth profiles, model registry, and session store. `agentDir` is the on-disk state directory that holds this per-agent config at `~/.openclaw/agents/<agentId>/`. A **binding** maps a channel account (e.g. a Slack workspace or a WhatsApp number) to one of those agents.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:100:    - WhatsApp: link each phone number per account.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:103:    openclaw channels login --channel whatsapp --account work\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:106:    See channel guides: [Discord](/channels/discord), [Telegram](/channels/telegram), [WhatsApp](/channels/whatsapp).\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:168:## One WhatsApp number, multiple people (DM split)\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:170:You can route **different WhatsApp DMs** to different agents while staying on **one WhatsApp account**. Match on sender E.164 (like `+15551234567`) with `peer.kind: \"direct\"`. Replies still come from the same WhatsApp number (no per-agent sender identity).\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:189:      match: { channel: \"whatsapp\", peer: { kind: \"direct\", id: \"+15551230001\" } },\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:193:      match: { channel: \"whatsapp\", peer: { kind: \"direct\", id: \"+15551230002\" } },\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:197:    whatsapp: {\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:207:- DM access control is **global per WhatsApp account** (pairing/allowlist), not per agent.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:257:Channels that support **multiple accounts** (e.g. WhatsApp) use `accountId` to identify each login. Each `accountId` can be routed to a different agent, so one server can host multiple phone numbers without mixing sessions.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:263:- `whatsapp`, `telegram`, `discord`, `slack`, `signal`, `imessage`\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:270:- `accountId`: one channel account instance (e.g. WhatsApp account `\"personal\"` vs `\"biz\"`).\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:361:  <Accordion title=\"WhatsApp numbers per agent\">\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:365:    openclaw channels login --channel whatsapp --account personal\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:366:    openclaw channels login --channel whatsapp --account biz\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:393:        { agentId: \"home\", match: { channel: \"whatsapp\", accountId: \"personal\" } },\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:394:        { agentId: \"work\", match: { channel: \"whatsapp\", accountId: \"biz\" } },\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:400:            channel: \"whatsapp\",\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:416:        whatsapp: {\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:419:              // Optional override. Default: ~/.openclaw/credentials/whatsapp/personal\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:420:              // authDir: \"~/.openclaw/credentials/whatsapp/personal\",\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:423:              // Optional override. Default: ~/.openclaw/credentials/whatsapp/biz\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:424:              // authDir: \"~/.openclaw/credentials/whatsapp/biz\",\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:438:  <Tab title=\"WhatsApp daily + Telegram deep work\">\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:439:    Split by channel: route WhatsApp to a fast everyday agent and Telegram to an Opus agent.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:460:        { agentId: \"chat\", match: { channel: \"whatsapp\" } },\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:468:    - If you have multiple accounts for a channel, add `accountId` to the binding (for example `{ channel: \"whatsapp\", accountId: \"personal\" }`).\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:473:    Keep WhatsApp on the fast agent, but route one DM to Opus:\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:496:          match: { channel: \"whatsapp\", peer: { kind: \"direct\", id: \"+15551234567\" } },\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:498:        { agentId: \"chat\", match: { channel: \"whatsapp\" } },\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:506:  <Tab title=\"Family agent bound to a WhatsApp group\">\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:507:    Bind a dedicated family agent to a single WhatsApp group, with mention gating and a tighter tool policy:\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md:544:            channel: \"whatsapp\",\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/streaming.md:44:- Channel hard cap: `*.textChunkLimit` (e.g., `channels.whatsapp.textChunkLimit`).\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/markdown-formatting.md:58:- Other channels (WhatsApp, iMessage, Microsoft Teams, Discord) still use plain text or\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/markdown-formatting.md:68:- `bullets`: convert each row into bullet points (default for Signal + WhatsApp).\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/messages.md:26:- Channel overrides (`channels.whatsapp.*`, `channels.telegram.*`, etc.) for caps and streaming toggles.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/messages.md:50:        whatsapp: 5000,\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/messages.md:177:- `messages.responsePrefix`, `channels.<channel>.responsePrefix`, and `channels.<channel>.accounts.<id>.responsePrefix` (outbound prefix cascade), plus `channels.whatsapp.messagePrefix` (WhatsApp inbound prefix)\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/agent.md:128:- `channels.whatsapp.allowFrom` (strongly recommended)\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/architecture.md:10:- A single long‑lived **Gateway** owns all messaging surfaces (WhatsApp via\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/architecture.md:17:- One Gateway per host; it is the only place that opens a WhatsApp session.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/model-providers.md:10:Reference for **LLM/model providers** (not chat channels like WhatsApp/Telegram). For model selection rules, see [Models](/concepts/models).\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/queue.md:108:- Applies to auto-reply agent runs across all inbound channels that use the gateway reply pipeline (WhatsApp web, Telegram, Slack, Discord, Signal, iMessage, webchat, etc.).\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/delegate-architecture.md:231:      match: { channel: \"whatsapp\", accountId: \"org\" },\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/delegate-architecture.md:239:    { agentId: \"main\", match: { channel: \"whatsapp\" } },\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/delegate-architecture.md:282:    { agentId: \"org-assistant\", match: { channel: \"whatsapp\", accountId: \"org\" } },\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/concepts/delegate-architecture.md:283:    { agentId: \"main\", match: { channel: \"whatsapp\" } },\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/btw.md:96:On channels like Telegram, WhatsApp, and Discord, BTW is delivered as a\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/multi-agent-sandbox-tools.md:63:            \"provider\": \"whatsapp\",\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/skills.md:305:    - Node installs honor `skills.install.nodeManager` in `openclaw.json` (default: npm; options: npm/pnpm/yarn/bun). This only affects skill installs; the Gateway runtime should still be Node — Bun is not recommended for WhatsApp/Telegram.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/reactions.md:50:  <Accordion title=\"WhatsApp\">\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/reactions.md:79:- [WhatsApp reactionLevel](/channels/whatsapp#reaction-level) — `channels.whatsapp.reactionLevel`\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/skills-config.md:95:  (Bun not recommended for WhatsApp/Telegram).\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/agent-send.md:41:    # Deliver to WhatsApp (default channel)\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/agent-send.md:62:| `--channel \\<name\\>`          | Delivery channel (whatsapp, telegram, discord, slack, etc.) |\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/slash-commands.md:65:  Enables parsing `/...` in chat messages. On surfaces without native commands (WhatsApp/WebChat/Signal/iMessage/Google Chat/Microsoft Teams), text commands still work even if you set this to `false`.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/slash-commands.md:352:/debug set channels.whatsapp.allowFrom=[\"+1555\",\"+4477\"]\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/elevated.md:46:            whatsapp: [\"+15555550123\"],\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/plugin.md:213:| WhatsApp        | `@openclaw/whatsapp`       | [WhatsApp](/channels/whatsapp)             |\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/diffs.md:494:- If your channel compresses images aggressively (for example Telegram or WhatsApp), prefer PDF output (`fileFormat: \"pdf\"`).\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/tts.md:12:and deliver native voice messages on Feishu, Matrix, Telegram, and WhatsApp,\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/tts.md:695:- **Feishu / WhatsApp**: when a voice-note reply is produced as MP3/WebM/WAV/M4A\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/tts.md:697:  Ogg/Opus with `ffmpeg` before sending the native voice message. WhatsApp sends\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/tts.md:700:  file as an attachment; WhatsApp send fails rather than posting an incompatible\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/tts.md:756:| Feishu / Matrix / Telegram / WhatsApp | Voice-note replies prefer **Opus** (`opus_48000_64` from ElevenLabs, `opus` from OpenAI). 48 kHz / 64 kbps balances clarity and size. |\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/tts.md:762:- **Feishu / WhatsApp transcoding:** When a voice-note reply lands as MP3/WebM/WAV/M4A, the channel plugin transcodes to 48 kHz Ogg/Opus with `ffmpeg`. WhatsApp sends through Baileys with `ptt: true` and `audio/ogg; codecs=opus`. If conversion fails: Feishu falls back to attaching the original file; WhatsApp send fails rather than posting an incompatible PTT payload.\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/tts.md:949:reply delivery. On Feishu, Matrix, Telegram, and WhatsApp, the audio is\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/tts.md:951:WhatsApp can transcode non-Opus TTS output on this path when `ffmpeg` is\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/tools/tts.md:954:WhatsApp sends audio through Baileys as a PTT voice note (`audio` with\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/logging.md:94:To filter channel activity (WhatsApp/Telegram/etc), use:\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/logging.md:97:openclaw channels logs --channel whatsapp\n/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/logging.md:123:- Subsystem prefixes (e.g. `gateway/channels/whatsapp`)"}],"details":{"persistedDetailsTruncated":true,"originalDetailsBytesAtLeast":8193,"originalDetailKeys":["status","exitCode","durationMs","aggregated","cwd"],"status":"completed","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspace-sharkzap","exitCode":0},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778729824466}}
{"type":"message","id":"1c64aa8b","parentId":"0e295e0a","timestamp":"2026-05-14T03:37:08.711Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_GZhdtrSwvcAzCvJUF5tMCp44|fc_080f36febbd39781016a054363f50c81968220fa0478da5d1b","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/channels/whatsapp.md","limit":220}}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.5","usage":{"input":3713,"output":35,"cacheRead":84480,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":88228,"cost":{"input":0.018565,"output":0.00105,"cacheRead":0.04224,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.061855}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778729824475,"responseId":"resp_080f36febbd39781016a054360e6688196a7963af36f1e10c7"}}
{"type":"message","id":"274a0377","parentId":"1c64aa8b","timestamp":"2026-05-14T03:37:08.723Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_GZhdtrSwvcAzCvJUF5tMCp44|fc_080f36febbd39781016a054363f50c81968220fa0478da5d1b","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nsummary: \"WhatsApp channel support, access controls, delivery behavior, and operations\"\nread_when:\n  - Working on WhatsApp/web channel behavior or inbox routing\ntitle: \"WhatsApp\"\n---\n\nStatus: production-ready via WhatsApp Web (Baileys). Gateway owns linked session(s).\n\n## Install (on demand)\n\n- Onboarding (`openclaw onboard`) and `openclaw channels add --channel whatsapp`\n  prompt to install the WhatsApp plugin the first time you select it.\n- `openclaw channels login --channel whatsapp` also offers the install flow when\n  the plugin is not present yet.\n- Dev channel + git checkout: defaults to the local plugin path.\n- Stable/Beta: uses the npm package `@openclaw/whatsapp` on the current official\n  release tag.\n\nManual install stays available:\n\n```bash\nopenclaw plugins install @openclaw/whatsapp\n```\n\nUse the bare package to follow the current official release tag. Pin an exact\nversion only when you need a reproducible install.\n\nOn Windows, the WhatsApp plugin needs Git on `PATH` during npm install because\none of its Baileys/libsignal dependencies is fetched from a git URL. Install\nGit for Windows, then restart the shell and rerun the install:\n\n```powershell\nwinget install --id Git.Git -e\n```\n\nPortable Git also works if its `bin` directory is on `PATH`.\n\n<CardGroup cols={3}>\n  <Card title=\"Pairing\" icon=\"link\" href=\"/channels/pairing\">\n    Default DM policy is pairing for unknown senders.\n  </Card>\n  <Card title=\"Channel troubleshooting\" icon=\"wrench\" href=\"/channels/troubleshooting\">\n    Cross-channel diagnostics and repair playbooks.\n  </Card>\n  <Card title=\"Gateway configuration\" icon=\"settings\" href=\"/gateway/configuration\">\n    Full channel config patterns and examples.\n  </Card>\n</CardGroup>\n\n## Quick setup\n\n<Steps>\n  <Step title=\"Configure WhatsApp access policy\">\n\n```json5\n{\n  channels: {\n    whatsapp: {\n      dmPolicy: \"pairing\",\n      allowFrom: [\"+15551234567\"],\n      groupPolicy: \"allowlist\",\n      groupAllowFrom: [\"+15551234567\"],\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step title=\"Link WhatsApp (QR)\">\n\n```bash\nopenclaw channels login --channel whatsapp\n```\n\n    For a specific account:\n\n```bash\nopenclaw channels login --channel whatsapp --account work\n```\n\n    To attach an existing/custom WhatsApp Web auth directory before login:\n\n```bash\nopenclaw channels add --channel whatsapp --account work --auth-dir /path/to/wa-auth\nopenclaw channels login --channel whatsapp --account work\n```\n\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step title=\"Start the gateway\">\n\n```bash\nopenclaw gateway\n```\n\n  </Step>\n\n  <Step title=\"Approve first pairing request (if using pairing mode)\">\n\n```bash\nopenclaw pairing list whatsapp\nopenclaw pairing approve whatsapp <CODE>\n```\n\n    Pairing requests expire after 1 hour. Pending requests are capped at 3 per channel.\n\n  </Step>\n</Steps>\n\n<Note>\nOpenClaw recommends running WhatsApp on a separate number when possible. (The channel metadata and setup flow are optimized for that setup, but personal-number setups are also supported.)\n</Note>\n\n## Deployment patterns\n\n<AccordionGroup>\n  <Accordion title=\"Dedicated number (recommended)\">\n    This is the cleanest operational mode:\n\n    - separate WhatsApp identity for OpenClaw\n    - clearer DM allowlists and routing boundaries\n    - lower chance of self-chat confusion\n\n    Minimal policy pattern:\n\n    ```json5\n    {\n      channels: {\n        whatsapp: {\n          dmPolicy: \"allowlist\",\n          allowFrom: [\"+15551234567\"],\n        },\n      },\n    }\n    ```\n\n  </Accordion>\n\n  <Accordion title=\"Personal-number fallback\">\n    Onboarding supports personal-number mode and writes a self-chat-friendly baseline:\n\n    - `dmPolicy: \"allowlist\"`\n    - `allowFrom` includes your personal number\n    - `selfChatMode: true`\n\n    In runtime, self-chat protections key off the linked self number and `allowFrom`.\n\n  </Accordion>\n\n  <Accordion title=\"WhatsApp Web-only channel scope\">\n    The messaging platform channel is WhatsApp Web-based (`Baileys`) in current OpenClaw channel architecture.\n\n    There is no separate Twilio WhatsApp messaging channel in the built-in chat-channel registry.\n\n  </Accordion>\n</AccordionGroup>\n\n## Runtime model\n\n- Gateway owns the WhatsApp socket and reconnect loop.\n- The reconnect watchdog uses WhatsApp Web transport activity, not only inbound app-message volume, so a quiet linked-device session is not restarted solely because nobody has sent a message recently. A longer application-silence cap still forces a reconnect if transport frames keep arriving but no application messages are handled for the watchdog window; after a transient reconnect for a recently active session, that application-silence check uses the normal message timeout for the first recovery window.\n- Baileys socket timings are explicit under `web.whatsapp.*`: `keepAliveIntervalMs` controls WhatsApp Web application pings, `connectTimeoutMs` controls the opening handshake timeout, and `defaultQueryTimeoutMs` controls Baileys query timeouts.\n- Outbound sends require an active WhatsApp listener for the target account.\n- Group sends attach native mention metadata for `@+<digits>` and `@<digits>` tokens in text and media captions when the token matches current WhatsApp participant metadata, including LID-backed groups.\n- Status and broadcast chats are ignored (`@status`, `@broadcast`).\n- The reconnect watchdog follows WhatsApp Web transport activity, not only inbound app-message volume: quiet linked-device sessions stay up while transport frames continue, but a transport stall forces reconnect well before the later remote disconnect path.\n- Direct chats use DM session rules (`session.dmScope`; default `main` collapses DMs to the agent main session).\n- Group sessions are isolated (`agent:<agentId>:whatsapp:group:<jid>`).\n- WhatsApp Channels/Newsletters can be explicit outbound targets with their native `@newsletter` JID. Outbound newsletter sends use channel session metadata (`agent:<agentId>:whatsapp:channel:<jid>`) rather than DM session semantics.\n- WhatsApp Web transport honors standard proxy environment variables on the gateway host (`HTTPS_PROXY`, `HTTP_PROXY`, `NO_PROXY` / lowercase variants). Prefer host-level proxy config over channel-specific WhatsApp proxy settings.\n- When `messages.removeAckAfterReply` is enabled, OpenClaw clears the WhatsApp ack reaction after a visible reply is delivered.\n\n## Plugin hooks and privacy\n\nWhatsApp inbound messages can contain personal message content, phone numbers,\ngroup identifiers, sender names, and session correlation fields. For that reason,\nWhatsApp does not broadcast inbound `message_received` hook payloads to plugins\nunless you explicitly opt in:\n\n```json5\n{\n  channels: {\n    whatsapp: {\n      pluginHooks: {\n        messageReceived: true,\n      },\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\nYou can scope the opt-in to one account:\n\n```json5\n{\n  channels: {\n    whatsapp: {\n      accounts: {\n        work: {\n          pluginHooks: {\n            messageReceived: true,\n          },\n        },\n      },\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\nOnly enable this for plugins you trust to receive inbound WhatsApp message\ncontent and identifiers.\n\n## Access control and activation\n\n<Tabs>\n  <Tab title=\"DM policy\">\n    `channels.whatsapp.dmPolicy` controls direct chat access:\n\n\n[499 more lines in file. Use offset=221 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1778729828722}}
